    "changes": [
      "`/api/*` HTTP responses are now gzip-compressed when your client sends `Accept-Encoding: gzip`. Most HTTP clients (browsers, `fetch`, `curl --compressed`, Python `requests`, Go `net/http`) do this automatically and transparently decompress — no code changes required. Large catalog endpoints like `/api/ships` shrink ~80%.",
      "Bandwidth-per-endpoint metrics on the admin dashboard will step-change lower for `/api/*` after this deploys (we now count compressed wire bytes, which is the correct measure). Not a traffic drop."
    ]
  },
